title: St. Johns River Springs and Seeps, Florida, 2007
name: St. Johns River Springs and Seeps, Florida, 2007
description: A spring is defined as a place where groundwater flows naturally onto the land surface or into a body of surface water. This data layer also includes surficial aquifer springs, which are now called seeps, under nomenclature recently agreed upon by the Florida Geological Survey. Springs will be derived from lat/longs stored in the Station Header table within the Oracle database; they are the subset of stations that represent springs. Individual representatives of a spring's group (for example, the many springs that make up the Silver Springs group) are each represented by a point, rather than a single point per group.
